title: Brunswick's losing skid grows to six with loss to Coffee County
text:
Brunswick's losing skid grows to six with loss to Coffee County 
By Mike Morrison Sat, Oct 17, 2015 @ 1:20 am 
BRUNSWICK — Coffee County tallied two touchdowns in the final minute of the first half to break a scoreless tie with Brunswick High. 
The visiting Trojans went on to win 27-3, handing the Pirates their sixth straight loss. 
Coffee’s Demeterius Davis scored on a 22-yard run with 57 seconds remaining in the second quarter and Alan Martinez booted the PAT to put the Trojans ahead 7-0. They added another touchdown 15 second later after Brunswick fumbled away the kickoff. 
Greg Williams ran 15 yards for the second touchdown, but the PAT failed after it was backed up 15 yards on a personal foul call. 
Coffee ground out 293 rushing yards and quarterback Max Hughes passed for 63 more as the Trojans of coach Robby Pruitt wore down Brunswick’s defense late in the game. Coffee added two fourth quarter touchdowns on a 1-yard Tywone Brewton plunge and a 2-yard run by Milton Jackson. 
Brunswick’s lone score came in the third quarter on a 41-yard Mitchell Finneran field goal. 
Brunswick’s first year coach, Larry Harold, said his team continues to be hampered by an arm injury to starting quarterback Randon Jernigan, who lined up at flanker for most of the game. He was at quarterback only for running plays, thereby tipping Coffee off as to what the upcoming play would be. 
“It makes our offense predictable and one-dimensional,” Harold said. “They loaded up the box against us on those plays.” 
Brunswick could muster only 116 total yards, 95 rushing and 21 passing. Alonzo Brown, a sophomore filling in for Jernigan, completed 5 of 11 passes, all to junior wide receiver Shawn Smith.Jernigan led the team in rushing with 12 carries for 34 yards. 
Davis ran 8 times for 79 yards for Coffee and Williams added 69 yards on 7 carries. 
Coffee continues to be at the top of Region 3- along with Glynn Academy and Ware County with only one region loss. The Trojans stand at 7-1 overall and 5-1 in the region.. Brunswick dropped to 1-6 overall and 0-5 in the region. 
Coffee County 27, Brunswick 3
